cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.CY 

This paper is focused on natural language processing and machine learning techniques for normalization of social media data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of word embeddings and a random forest classifier, which are common techniques in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, such as N-gram features, which could place it in the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the generalizability and efficiency of the proposed model, which could place it in the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. Finally, the paper involves the use of spelling correction, which could place it in the cs.CY (Computational Linguistics) category.
